# CODEOWNERS — the hard human-review backstop for the unattended auto-merge pipeline.
#
# With "Require review from Code Owners" enabled in the branch ruleset (see
# docs/auto-merge.md), any PR that touches a code-owned path below needs an actual
# code owner's approval before it can merge. The fleet/automation bot is NOT a code
# owner, so it physically cannot self-approve these — the dangerous ~5% of paths stop
# for a human while everything else flows through the checks-only green path.
#
# Last match wins (GitHub CODEOWNERS semantics). Keep these globs in lockstep with any
# risky-path pre-filter in the auto-merge automation; CODEOWNERS is the authoritative stop.

# Default: no owner -> agent path, gated only by the `verify` checks (this is intended).

# CI/CD, the gates themselves, secret usage, this very file. Includes the auto-merge
# guardrail workflows (merge-guard, llm-review) — an agent must never weaken its own gates.
/.github/                @Eyalm321

# The LLM-judge gate script: a malicious edit here could rewrite the rubric / fail-open the
# qualitative reviewer, so it is a hard human-review path even though it sits outside .github/.
/scripts/llm-review.sh   @Eyalm321

# GPU/GUI surface — heavy, hardware-dependent, not exercised by the per-PR test gate.
/rs/crates/app/          @Eyalm321

# Auth / token surface — minting and validating control-plane tokens. A bad change here can
# hand out or accept forged credentials; never auto-merge it.
/rs/crates/core/src/control/tokens.rs   @Eyalm321

# The control server + its routing/scope/lock = the network-exposed control plane and its
# authorization boundary. Risky enough to require a human.
/rs/crates/core/src/control/server.rs   @Eyalm321
/rs/crates/core/src/control/routes.rs   @Eyalm321
/rs/crates/core/src/control/scope.rs    @Eyalm321

# Session lifecycle: PTY spawn + the daemon transport run other processes with the user's
# privileges. A subtle change is a privilege/RCE surface — human review required.
/rs/crates/core/src/session/   @Eyalm321

# Secret redaction for the AI/telemetry path. Weakening this can leak secrets off the box.
/rs/crates/core/src/ai/redactor.rs   @Eyalm321

# build.rs = arbitrary code execution at build time.
**/build.rs              @Eyalm321

# Dependency / supply-chain changes.
**/Cargo.toml            @Eyalm321
**/Cargo.lock            @Eyalm321
